---
scope: deploy/
description: Deploy aidemd.dev as a zero-runtime static export to GitHub Pages with a custom domain, triggered on push to master.
intent: >
  Deploy aidemd.dev to GitHub Pages as a fully static site. The build
  produces a zero-runtime export (next export) served from GitHub Pages
  with the custom domain aidemd.dev. Deployment triggers automatically
  on push to master. No server, no runtime, no edge functions — the
  site is a static artifact and GitHub Pages is the only hosting target.
outcomes:
  desired:
    - Pushing to master triggers a GitHub Actions workflow that builds the Next.js static export and deploys it to GitHub Pages with zero manual steps.
    - The site is reachable at https://aidemd.dev with the custom domain configured in GitHub Pages; all existing routes (/, /docs, /docs/[slug]) resolve correctly as static HTML files.
    - sitemap.xml and robots.txt are generated at build time and included in the static output.
  undesired:
    - Any runtime dependency — the deployed site must not require a Node.js server, edge runtime, or serverless functions. If the build fails because a feature is incompatible with static export, that feature must be removed or replaced, not worked around with a server.
    - A broken font pipeline — next/font/google must produce self-hosted font files in the static output, not runtime requests to Google Fonts.
    - Deploy workflow that runs on branches other than master, or that deploys without a successful build step gating it.
---
